d%20suitable%20for%20those%20with%20sensitive%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20with%20SPF%3A%20EltaMD%20UV%20Clear%20Broad-Spectrum%20SPF%2046%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20versatile%20option%20that's%20one-part%20sunscreen%20and%20one-part%20moisturizer%2C%20Dr.%20Wesley%20suggests%20the%20EltaMD%20UV%20Clear%20Broad-Spectrum%20SPF%2046.%20The%20niacinamide%2C%20hyaluronic%20acid%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ffitness%2Flactic-acid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elactic%20acid%3C%2Fa%3E%20provide%20plenty%20of%20moisture%20to%20keep%20oily%20skin%20hydrated%20without%20any%20icky%20greasy%20residue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20lightweight%3A%20Murad%20Oil%20and%20Pore%20Control%20Mattifier%20Broad%20Spectrum%20SPF%2045%3Cp%3EMurad's%20Oil%20and%20Pore%20Control%20Mattifier%20Broad%20Spectrum%20SPF%2045%20is%20an%20oil-free%2C%20ultra-light%20SPF%20moisturizer.%20It%20even%20doubles%20as%20a%20mattifying%20primer.%20And%2C%20since%20it's%20free%20of%20parabens%2C%20sulfates%2C%20and%20phthalates%2C%20it's%20also%20suitable%20for%20sensitive%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20nighttime%3A%20Paula's%20Choice%20Water-Infusing%20Electrolyte%20Moisturizer%3Cp%3EPaula's%20Choice%20Water-Infusing%20Electrolyte%20Moisturizer%20was%20specially%20formulated%20to%20quench%20thirsty%20skin%20while%20you%20snooze.%20The%20lightweight%20cream%20is%20enriched%20with%20electrolytes%20to%20boost%20hydration%2C%20while%20other%20ingredient%20highlights%20include%20fatty%20acid-rich%20ceramides%20and%20antioxidant-loaded%20fruit%20extracts.%20Come%20the%20AM%2C%20you'll%20have%20plump%2C%20dewy%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBest%20gel%20cream%3A%20Tatcha%20The%20Water%20Cream%3Cp%3EWith%20its%20signature%20gel-cream%20texture%20that%20absorbs%20instantly%20into%20the%20skin%2C%20Tatcha's%20The%20Water%20Cream%20is%2C%20hands%20down%2C%20one%20of%20the%20best%20moisturizers%20for%20oily%20skin.%20Its%20oil-free%20formula%20%E2%80%94%20enriched%20with%20glycerin%2C%20green%20tea%2C%20and%20even%20real%20gold%20%E2%80%94%20can%20help%20minimize%20the%20appearance%20of%20pores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20our%20full%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Ftatcha-water-cream-review%5C%22%3ETatcha%20Water%20Cream%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20to%20look%20for%3Cp%3ELook%20for%20lightweight%20formulas%20when%20shopping%20for%20the%20best%20moisturizers%20for%20oily%20skin.%20Think%20water-based%20gels%2C%20lotions%2C%20and%20thin%2C%20silky%20creams%20instead%20of%20richer%2C%20thicker%2C%20and%20heavier%20options.%20And%20while%20lotions%20and%20creams%20are%20sometimes%20used%20interchangeably%2C%20it's%20worth%20mentioning%20that%20the%20former%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20higher%20water%20content.%20According%20to%20Dr.%20Zeichner%2C%20folks%20with%20oily%20skin%20should%20opt%20for%20moisturizers%20enriched%20with%20humectants%20(such%20as%20hyaluronic%20acid%20and%20glycerin%2C%20for%20example)%20rather%20than%20emollients%20and%20occlusives%2C%20which%20tend%20to%20be%20heavier.%20Per%20Zeichner%2C%20humectants%20help%20bring%20water%20to%20the%20top%20layer%20of%20the%20skin%20for%20hydration.%20Non-comedogenic%2C%20oil-free%20formulas%20are%20also%20especially%20great%20for%20those%20with%20oily%20skin%20since%20they%20won't%20clog%20your%20pores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFAQs%3Ch3%3EWhat%20causes%20oily%20skin%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20oily%20skin%20can%20be%20genetic%2C%20both%20dermatologists%20tell%20Insider%20that%20things%20like%20diet%2C%20stress%2C%20hormones%2C%20and%20the%20wrong%20products%20can%20also%20impact%20your%20sebum%20levels.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20foods%20high%20in%20sugar%20and%20cow's%20milk%2C%20particularly%20skim%20milk%2C%20stimulate%20oil%20gland%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Zeichner%20says.%20Teenagers%20are%20also%20prone%20to%20oiliness%2C%20thanks%20to%20fluctuating%20hormones%20during%20puberty.%20Over-exfoliating%20or%20using%20the%20wrong%20product%20for%20your%20skin%20can%20also%20cause%20oily%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Zeichner%20clarifies%20that%20those%20with%20oily%20skin%20are%20typically%20shiny%20all%20over%20the%20face%2C%20whereas%20combination%20skin%20types%20commonly%20have%20oily%20T-zones%20and%20dry%20cheeks.%20The%20center%20of%20your%20face%20(the%20forehead%2C%20nose%2C%20and%20chin)%2C%20known%20as%20the%20T-zone%2C%20is%20where%20you'll%20find%20the%20most%20oil%20glands.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20I%20know%20if%20I%20have%20oily%20skin%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20test%2C%20wash%20your%20face%20and%20then%20wait%20three%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Zeichner%20says.%20%26quot%3BThen%2C%20look%20back%20in%20the%20mirror%3B%20if%20you%20look%20shiny%2C%20you%20likely%20have%20oily%20skin.%26quot%3B%20If%20you%20suspect%20your%20skin%20is%20oily%2C%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20chat%20with%20your%20dermatologist%20before%20making%20any%20major%20changes%20to%20your%20skin-care%20routine.%20They'll%20be%20able%20to%20give%20you%20pointers%20on%20how%20to%20manage%20your%20oily%20skin%20and%20what%20types%20of%20products%20to%20look%20for%20(and%20steer%20clear%20of!).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20oily%20skin%20also%20acne-prone%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20overproduction%20of%20oil%20can%20lead%20to%20acne%2C%20the%20two%20terms%20are%20not%20synonymous.%20%26quot%3BHaving%20oily%20skin%20does%20not%20necessarily%20mean%20that%20you%20are%20acne-prone%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dr.%20Zeichner.%20He%20continues%2C%20telling%20Insider%3A%20%26quot%3BYour%20genetics%20determines%20acne%2C%20and%20it's%20caused%20by%20various%20factors%2C%20including%20acne-causing%20bacteria%2C%20as%20well%20as%20skin%20cells%20that%20stick%20together%20and%20block%20the%20pores.%26quot%3B%20So%2C%20it's%20certainly%20possible%20to%20have%20oily%20skin%20without%20experiencing%20breakouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EShould%20I%20use%20acne-fighting%20ingredients%20in%20my%20moisturizer%20if%20I%20have%20oily%20skin%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Dr.%20Wesley%2C%20it's%20important%20not%20to%20over-dry%20your%20skin.%20Instead%2C%20find%20moisturizers%20with%20beta-hydroxy%20acids%20like%20salicylic%20acid%20and%20alpha-hydroxy%20acids%20like%20glycolic%20acid.%20These%20types%20of%20acids%20can%20take%20care%20of%20all%20the%20extra%20oil%20and%20assist%20in%20unblocking%20pores.%20%26quot%3BTopical%20vitamin%20A%20derivatives%2C%20such%20as%20retinol%20and%20retinoids%2C%20help%20decrease%20oil%20gland%20production%20with%20continued%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Just%20know%20that%20visible%20changes%20take%20time%20to%20appear%20and%20won't%20emerge%20overnight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhich%20ingredients%20won't%2Fwill%20make%20my%20skin%20oilier%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20avoid%20comedogenic%20oils%2C%20as%20they%20clog%20pores%20and%20can%20lead%20to%20even%20more%20acne.%20One%20oil%20that%20doesn't%20tend%20to%20clog%20pores%20is%20jojoba.%20%26quot%3BSome%20oils%20that%20have%20a%20good%20balance%20of%20linoleic%20acid%20over%20oleic%20acids%20help%20to%20match%20or%20balance%20our%20skin's%20natural%20fatty%20acid%20composition%20and%20can%20be%20helpful%20for%20oily%20skin%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Wesley%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-face-moisturizers-oily-skin%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705962616000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65aee5cc43bb77284b9f85d0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-fa