on-dock%5C%22%3EChinese%20research%20vessels%20had%20visited%3C%2Fa%3E%20neighbouring%20Sri%20Lanka.%20Defence%20sources%20stated%20that%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20is%20monitoring%20the%20activity%20of%20the%20ship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Chinese%20research%20vessel%20Yuan%20Wang%205%20docked%20at%20Hambantota%2C%20while%20another%20ship%20Shi%20Yan%20stayed%20for%20several%20days%20at%20Colombo%20port%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESri%20Lanka%20declared%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fsri-lanka-india-china-research-ships-42ddb725105eb32b3b43fee8fff3838c%5C%22%3Eone-year%20moratorium%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20entry%20of%20all%20research%20vessels%20into%20its%20waters.%20While%20the%20official%20explanation%20cited%20the%20need%20to%20enhance%20capacity%20to%20manage%20foreign%20research%20vessels%2C%20the%20decision%20coincided%20with%20Colombo%20feeling%20pressured%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomynext.com%2Fsri-lanka-to-build-foreign-research-ship-handling-capacity-amid-1-year-ban-sources-146214%2F%5C%22%3Ebeing%20sandwiched%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20between%20the%20two%20Asian%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Sri%20Lanka%20has%20implemented%20a%20temporary%20ban%2C%20the%20Chinese%20research%20vessel%20is%20likely%20to%20receive%20a%20welcome%20in%20the%20Maldives.%20The%20new%20Maldives%20government%20under%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20has%20strained%20ties%20with%20India%20since%20taking%20over%20after%20the%20elections%20last%20November%2C%20demanding%20the%20removal%20of%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20stationed%20to%20operate%20three%20donated%20aircraft%20for%20humanitarian%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Muizzu%20also%20went%20for%20his%20first%20state%20visit%20in%20foreign%20country%20to%20China%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20which%20was%20the%20first%20time%20that%20a%20democratically%20elected%20president%20of%20the%20archipelago%20nation%20had%20not%20chosen%20India%20as%20first%20port%20of%20call%20after%20election.%20Separately%2C%20a%20senior%20official%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20China%20met%20with%20Muizzu%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpresidency.gov.mv%2FPress%2FArticle%2F29681%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpresidency.gov.mv%2FPress%2FArticle%2F29681%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3Eon%20Monday%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famti.csis.org%2Fa-survey-of-marine-research-vessels-in-the-indo-pacific%2F%5C%22%3EA%202020%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Washington-based%20think%20tank%20CSIS%20on%20Chinese%20research%20vessel%20activities%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20highlighted%20that%20such%20research%20could%20serve%20both%20civilian%20and%20military%20purposes.%20The%20collection%20of%20undersea%20data%20is%20considered%20crucial%20for%20detecting%20submarines%2C%20making%20it%20vital%20for%20naval%20reconnaissance.%20Consequently%2C%20the%20routes%20taken%20by%20Chinese%20research%20vessels%20have%20been%20closely%20examined%20for%20any%20tell-tale%20behaviour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffeatures.csis.org%2Fhiddenreach%2Fchina-indian-ocean-research-vessels%2F%5C%22%3EA%20new%20report%20by%20CSIS%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20same%20topic%20released%20earlier%20this%20month%20observed%20that%20many%20of%20the%20research%20vessels%20are%20owned%20and%20operated%20by%20state-affiliated%20organisations%20with%20close%20ties%20to%20the%20Chinese%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20research%20group%20wrote%20that%20Xiang%20Yang%20Hong%20class%20vessels%20were%20earlier%20overseen%20by%20China%E2%80%99s%20State%20Oceanic%20Administration%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.xinhuanet.com%2Fenglish%2F2017-04%2F21%2Fc_136225983.htm%5C%22%3Elinked%20to%20the%20PLA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20is%20now%20under%20institutes%20of%20the%20Chinese%20Ministry%20of%20Natural%20Resources%20(MNR)%2C%20which%20is%20also%20closely%20tied%20to%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%202020%20report%2C%20Xiang%20Yang%20Hong%2003%2C%20the%20Chinese%20ship%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20on%20the%20way%20to%20Mal%C3%A9%2C%20had%20four%20years%20ago%20circulated%20within%2030%20nautical%20miles%20of%20the%20US%20territories%20of%20Guam%20and%20Northern%20Mariana%20islands%20and%20conducted%20bathymetric%20survey%20in%20waters%20that%20included%20part%20of%20the%20US%20extended%20economic%20zone.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20it%20also%20appeared%20to%20be%20conducting%20research%20near%20Hawaii%2C%20before%20suddenly%20changing%20its%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20previously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fafter-india-us-raises-concern-with-sri-lanka-over-the-visit-of-chinese-research-vessel%5C%22%3Eraised%20objection%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Sri%20Lanka%20over%20the%20visit%20of%20Chinese%20research%20vessels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20day%20earlier%2C%20the%20Commander%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20Command%2C%20Admiral%20John%20Aquilino%2C%20had%20met%20with%20the%20Maldivian%20leadership%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20public%20mention%20of%20any%20contentious%20issue%20being%20raised%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpresidency.gov.mv%2FPress%2FArticle%2F29671%5C%22%3Ereadouts%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESymon%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fdetresfa_%2Fstatus%2F1749427302923223162%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eposted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Xiang%20Yang%20Hong%2003%20had%20been%20surveying%20in%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20since%20November%202019%20and%20in%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%20a%20year%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EXIANG%20YANG%20HONG%2003%20the%20Chinese%20ocean%20research%20vessel%20heading%20to%20Male%2C%20Maldives%20is%20no%20stranger%20to%20the%20region%